data.content:
Works perfectly. Here's the full program:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("Alice", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,
    WriteIndented = true
};

string json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

**Key point:** `JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` is a built-in policy (added alongside `SnakeCaseLower`, `KebabCaseLower`, etc.). It converts the lowercase record parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) in the JSON output — no custom policy class needed.
